    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The free peoples side is almost pure archery. Once you have a bow on Elrond and Arwen with Splendour on Elrond, you can easily have 5 archery a turn, healing your companions with Shadow Between, and discarding your extra copies of Elrond to heal him. If anything survives past the archery phase, Smeagol can fight them, or Arwen can, she&#39;s a 13 strength against fierce minions, and can cycle through your extra cards. Foul Creation and Curse Their Foul Feet help out against trackers and Moria archery, or even Sauron, if you can&#39;t use them they&#39;re fodder for Gwemegil and Shadow Between. Legs can fight as well once he has his weapons, and the Tale can let you kill most minions with him. Vilya can bounce conditions back your opponent&#39;s hand, clogging it, and provides Elrond with an extra exertion. <br />
For the shadow, it&#39;s the patented Dunland site control. Early game, try to drop a Saruman and Hillman Tribe, it&#39;s teh most fool-proof way to take control of a site. You want to bid high enough to win, since you must also add a burden for Smeagol I generally bid 2, but you can bid higher if you want. Stack Dunlendings on sites, the shadow number becomes +5 with No Refuge, and make them double with no retreat and pull the Horde with Constantly THreatening.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
